NXP's Yocto BSP with Kodi (XBMC) supported
===============================
This builds the Kodi (XBMC) demo image based on the YoctoBSP of i.MX6 SOC with GPU hardware.

The image can only run on the i.MX6 QualPlus SabreSD board. 
It is simply a demo showing that Kodi (XBMC) runs. It is not supported nor tested.

To get the BSP you need to have `repo` installed and use it as:

Install the `repo` utility (only need to do once):
--------------------------------------------------

$: mkdir ~/bin
$: curl http://commondatastorage.googleapis.com/git-repo-downloads/repo  > ~/bin/repo
$: chmod a+x ~/bin/repo
$: PATH=${PATH}:~/bin

Download the BSP Yocto Project Environment into your directory:
---------------------------------------------------------------

$: mkdir imx-xbmc-demo
$: cd imx-xbmc-demo
$: repo init -u git://git.freescale.com/imx/fsl-arm-yocto-bsp.git -b imx-4.1.15-1.0.0_xbmc-demo
$: repo sync

Configure the build (These scripts should be run only once for a specific build directory):
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Setup for Frame Buffer graphical backend.
$: MACHINE=imx6qpsabresd DISTRO=fsl-imx-fb source ./fsl-setup-release.sh -b xbmc-fb
$: source ../nxp-xbmc-setup.sh

Build an XBMC image:
--------------------
bitbake nxp-image-xbmc-demo
